<h2><a name="sign_in_registration"></a><a name="activate"></a>Sign Up and Log In</h2>

<p><a name="join"></a><span class="subhead_plain_bold">How can I sign up on <%=aname%>?</span>
To join <%=aname%> as a member, click "Sign Up" at the top right corner of any page, or simply <%= link_to 'sign up here', "/members/new/" + (params[:popup] ? '" target="_blank' : "") %>. After entering your name, password and other required information, you will receive an email invitation to activate your account. Click on the link in your email invitation &ndash; this will take you to your account page, where you may fill out your profile in more detail, or start reviewing stories on our home page. This invitation link can only be used once, so please activate your account right away and do not forward it to anyone.</p>
<p>
Note: If you are a Facebook member, we recommend you sign up with <%= link_to 'Facebook Connect','#facebook' %>, which lets you share your reviews with your friends on Facebook.</p> 

<p><a name="register"></a><span class="subhead_plain_bold">How do I activate my account?</span>
When you receive an email invitation asking you to activate your account, click on the link in your invitation, and follow the instructions on the next page. You will need to enter a password of your choice to activate your account. If you've already signed up before, you do not need to sign up again; click on "<%= link_to 'Log in', "/sessions/new/" + (params[:popup] ? '" target="_blank' : "") %>" instead.</p>
<p>
If you do not receive an email from <%=aname%> upon signing up, it may have been removed by your email provider's junk mail filter. Check your email's spam or junk mail folder for an email from <%=aname%>. If you need additional help, contact us at <%= mail_to email_addr("help"), email_addr("help"), :subject => "#{aname} help request", :encode => "javascript" %>.</p>
<p>
Alternately, if you have a Facebook account, you can finish signing up using <%= link_to 'Facebook Connect','#facebook_log_in_member' %>.</p>

<p><a name="invitation_expired"></a><span class="subhead_plain_bold">What if my invitation expired?</span>
Your invitation link to join <%=aname%> can only be used once. Once it has been used to activate a member account, it automatically expires. If you clicked your invitation link a second time, you will see a message that your invitation has expired. If you've already activated your account, click on "Log In" at the top right corner of any page on our site. If you were not able to log in, please email us at  <%= mail_to email_addr("invites"), email_addr("invites"), :subject => "#{aname} Invite request", :encode => "javascript" %> to request another invitation.</p>

<p><a name="sign_in"></a><span class="subhead_plain_bold">How do I log in to <%=aname%>?</span>
Once you activate your account, you will be automatically logged in to <%=aname%>, as long as you use the same computer and JavaScript-enabled browser. To log in to <%=aname%> on a different computer or browser, click on the "<%= link_to 'Log In', "/sessions/new/" + (params[:popup] ? '" target="_blank' : "") %>" link at the top right corner of any <%=aname%> page. Then enter your email address and password. Once you log in, your member name will be displayed at the top right corner of each page (along with a link to <%= link_to 'My Account', "/members/my_account/" + (params[:popup] ? '" target="_blank' : "") %>, where you can set your personal preferences). If you aren't a <%=aname%> member yet, you first need to <%= link_to 'sign up', "/members/new/" + (params[:popup] ? '" target="_blank' : "") %> and activate your account, as described above.</a></p>
<p>
Note: If you are a Facebook member, we recommend you log in with <%= link_to 'Facebook Connect','#facebook' %>, which lets you share your reviews with your friends on Facebook.</p>

<p><a name="sign_out"></a><span class="subhead_plain_bold">How do I log out from <%=aname%>?</span>
To log out from <%=aname%>, click on the "Log Out" link at the top right corner of any <%=aname%> page, next to your member name and "<%= link_to 'My Account', "/members/my_account/" + (params[:popup] ? '" target="_blank' : "") %>" links. If you are using a public computer, we recommend you always log out at the end of a session, to protect your privacy. Also, please log out if you see someone else's name at the top right corner of any <%=aname%> page. You can quickly log in again, anytime you like, by clicking on "Log In", as described above.</p>

<p><a name="lost_password"></a><span class="subhead_plain_bold">What if I forgot my password?</span>
If you forget your password, click on "<%= link_to 'Forgot Your Password?', "/sessions/forgot_password/" + (params[:popup] ? '" target="_blank' : "") %>" at the bottom of the Log in form. A new password will be emailed to the address you gave us earlier.</p>

<td class="subhead_plain"><a name="why_full_name"></a><span class="subhead_plain_bold">Why do I have to give my full name?</span>
To insure the integrity of our reviews, we ask that every member identify themselves with their real first and last name only. We do not allow anonymous or pseudonymous posts on <%=aname%> at this time. Please do not sign up or activate your account if you do not agree with this term of service.</p>

<p><a name="why_email_address"></a><span class="subhead_plain_bold">How will my email address be used?</span>
Your email address will only be used for purposes you specifically authorize (see our <%= link_to 'privacy policy', "/about/privacy/", :class => "popup_link" %>). If you are a registered member, your email address will be used for identification purposes during the sign-in process, and to inform you about any changes to your account or new developments at <%=aname%>.</p>

<p>By default, your email address is kept private and is not shown on your member profile. If you wish to show your email address in your profile, click on "<%= link_to 'My Account', "/members/my_account/" + (params[:popup] ? '" target="_blank' : "") %>" in the top navigation bar, then check "Show on Profile" next to your email address in "My Account" form. If you do not wish to show your email in your profile, uncheck "Show on Profile" next to your email.
</p>


<p><a name="manage_emails"></a><span class="subhead_plain_bold">How can I manage emails I receive from <%=aname%>?</span>
All members are included in our general mailing list, and automatically receive our daily, weekly, and special notices email newsletter by default. To change your email settings, or unsubscribe from our general mailings, click on "<%= link_to 'My Account', "/members/my_account/" + (params[:popup] ? '" target="_blank' : "") %>" at the top right of any page on our site and click on the Emails tab, or go directly to our <%= link_to 'Email Feeds page', "/email/" + (params[:popup] ? '" target="_blank' : "") %>. Then select the newsletter options of your choice and click "Save."</p>

<p>You can select any or all of these types of emails from <%=aname%>:</p>
<div class="sect_indent"> 
  <p><a name="member_daily_newsletter"></a><span class="subhead_italic_med">Daily Newsletter</span>
  Checking the "Daily Newsletter" box allows <%=aname%> to send you a daily selection of news and opinions from our most trusted sources. Includes today's Most Recent and Most Trusted stories and is sent <%=Newsletter.humanized_dispatch_time(Newsletter::DAILY, :no_sent => true)%>. If you do not wish to receive the Daily Newsletter, simply uncheck "Daily Newsletter."</p>
  
  <p><a name="member_mynews"></a><span class="subhead_italic_med"><%= mynews_colors() %> Daily Email</span>
  Checking "<%= mynews_colors() %> Daily Email" will deliver your personalized news feed <%=Newsletter.humanized_dispatch_time(Newsletter::MYNEWS, :no_sent => true)%>. You must first set up your <%= link_to "MyNews page", "/mynews/" + (params[:popup] ? '" target="_blank' : "") %>, which only takes a minute. To learn more about MyNews, <%= link_to 'click here', "/help/faq/mynews/" + (params[:popup] ? "?popup=true" : "") %>.</p>
  
  <p><a name="member_weekly_newsletter"></a><span class="subhead_italic_med">Weekly Newsletter</span>
  Checking the "Weekly Newsletter" box allows <%=aname%> to send you a weekly selection of quality news and opinions, based on ratings from members like you. Includes this week's Most Recent and Most Trusted stories, as well as helpful tips and news about <%=aname%>. <%=Newsletter.humanized_dispatch_time(Newsletter::WEEKLY)%>. We highly recommend this option, so you can stay up-to-date. If you do not wish to receive the Weekly Newsletter, simply uncheck "Weekly Newsletter."</p>
  
  <p><a name="member_additional_email"></a><span class="subhead_italic_med">Special Notices</span>
  From time to time, we may send out additional emails to you with helpful tips and news about <%=aname%>. If you do not wish to receive these notices, simply uncheck this box.</p>
</div>

<p><a name="privacy_policy"></a><span class="subhead_plain_bold">What is your privacy policy?</span>
