<h2><a name="community_questions%22"></a><a name="community_questions"></a>Community Questions</h2>

<p><a name="community_guidelines"></a><span class="subhead_plain_bold">What are your community guidelines?</span>
Our community guidelines are simple: treat each other with respect, only share information that adds value to our community, do not harass other members or news sources, and adhere to our terms of service.</p>

<p><a name="terms_of_service"></a><span class="subhead_plain_bold">What are your terms of service?</span>
By registering as a member of <%=aname%>, you agree to our terms of service and community guidelines. Our terms of service ask that you be courteous, respect others' privacy, and provide your full name and a valid email address, and prohibit disruptive or offensive behavior, solicitation, plagiarism and copyright infringement. If you are involved in a story, our terms also require that you disclose any potential conflict of interest. For more information, check our full <%= link_to 'terms of service', "/about/terms/" + (params[:popup] ? "?popup=true" : "") %>. Thanks for your patience and understanding during this beta phase.
</p>

<p><a name="what_is_host"></a><span class="subhead_plain_bold">What is a host?</span>
A host is an active and trusted member of our community who has been selected by <%=aname%> staff to help edit our site and moderate topics on <%=aname%>. Hosts are responsible for leading new members by example, reviewing frequently and posting stories for their topics, as well as checking the information in story reviews and editing it as needed.</p>

<p><a name="host_signup"></a><span class="subhead_plain_bold">How can I become a host?</span>
If you would like to help edit our site and/or host a news topic or comments about specific news sources, we would love to hear from you. To become a host you must have reviewed at least 10 stories in the past month, and have a member validation score of four or more. You should be familiar with our site (for general hosts) and have some fluency in the topic you're interested in hosting (for topic hosts). Hosts typically spend a couple hours each week to help edit our site and moderate your topic, on a volunteer basis. To apply as a host, email  <%= mail_to email_addr("hosts"), email_addr("hosts"), :subject => "#{aname} Host Request", :encode => "javascript" %>.</p>

<p><a name="invite_a_friend"></a><span class="subhead_plain_bold">Can I invite friends to join <%=aname%>?</span>
If you have a friend, colleague or relative that you think would be interested in participating in <%=aname%>, and you're already a <%=aname%> member, click "<%= link_to 'Invite', "/members/invite/" + (params[:popup] ? '" target="_blank' : "") %>" in our bottom navbar.</p>
